  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  &gt; 21 years of age

          -  Primary arterial hypertension

          -  Office blood pressure between 140/90 mmHg and 160/100 mmHg

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Participation in another clinical study

          -  Unstable clinical condition

          -  Secondary arterial hypertension

          -  Dementia

          -  Major disability (modified Rankin-Scale &gt; 4)

          -  Severe chronic kidney disease (serum creatinine &gt; 2.0 mg/dL or estimated glomerular
             filtration rate &lt; 40 ml/min/1.73m2)

          -  Liver disease including history of hepatic encephalopathy, esophageal varices or
             portacaval shunt

          -  History of gastrointestinal operation or disease with a potential influence on drug
             absorption

          -  Allergy or other contraindications against drugs given during the study

          -  History of non-compliance
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
